# Architecture

The authoritative descriptions of architecture and module layout now live in:

- `docs/gnucash_email_receipt_categorization_spec.mdc` (components, data flow, LLM interaction)
- `docs/developers_guide.mdc` (codebase structure, external dependencies, testing expectations)

`docs/architecture_implementation_plan.mdc` is intentionally kept as a lightweight pointer to those
two documents and should not introduce additional facts.

Quick data flow reminder (see spec + developers guide for full details):

- `run` → load GnuCash → filter candidates → index emails → OCR receipts → match → predict → save proposals
- `review` → Flask web app → one-by-one approval with evidence checkboxes → persist decisions
- `apply` → load decisions → backup → write XML (descriptions + split accounts) → audit + journal
